    ### Scope Extension — Skill Consumer Upgrades (Added post-publication)
    
    > **Note**: This extension was added after the original FR-ADHOC-010 was published. The skill-scaffolding work (ACs 1-10) is the floor; the work in this extension is the ceiling of this issue. No follow-up issue is required for the scope covered here.
    
    - **Extended Description**: In addition to the three new skill templates (`deviate-flows`, `deviate-architecture`, `deviate-release`), this issue also upgrades the two existing DeviaTDD skills that emit issue files — `deviate-shard` (`src/deviate/prompts/skills/deviate-shard/SKILL.md`) and `deviate-adhoc` (`src/deviate/prompts/skills/deviate-adhoc/SKILL.md`) — so they (a) consume the new `_product` specs (`specs/_product/flows/`, `specs/_product/architecture.md`, `specs/_product/release-next.md`) as authoritative context and (b) emit `flow_refs: [FLOW-XX, ...]` in the YAML frontmatter of every issue file they generate. The `deviate adhoc pre` CLI command at `src/deviate/cli/adhoc.py:45-83` gains a `--flow-ref FLOW-01,FLOW-02` Typer option that propagates to the `AdhocRecord.flow_refs` field. The `IssueRecord` Pydantic model in `src/deviate/state/ledger.py` gains an optional `flow_refs: list[str] = Field(default_factory=list)` field; `validate_yaml_frontmatter` at `src/deviate/cli/macro.py:41` recognizes `flow_refs` as a known key; and `_compute_next_issue_id`/`append_issue_record` at `src/deviate/cli/macro.py:177-204, 682-700` thread the field through to `specs/issues.jsonl` round-trip serialization. This is a self-contained scope addition — no follow-up issue needed.
    - **Extended Inputs/Outputs**: Input — `--flow-ref FLOW-01,FLOW-02` CLI flag for `deviate adhoc pre`; FR→flow mapping derived from `specs/_product/flows/flows-product.md` during shard execution. Output — `flow_refs:` populated in every emitted issue frontmatter; `IssueRecord.flow_refs` populated in every `specs/issues.jsonl` JSONL line; `AdhocRecord.flow_refs` populated in every `specs/adhoc.jsonl` JSONL line.
    
    ### Acceptance Criteria (Extended Scope)
